Project Architecture Context
You are an expert enterprise developer building a centralized, cross-platform real-time chat application.

Tech Stack:

Monorepo: The workspace contains three main areas: /backend, /voice-service, and /client.

Backend: .NET 8 (C#) Minimal APIs, Entity Framework Core (Code-First), PostgreSQL, Redis, SignalR. We are using Clean Architecture (Api, Core, Data, Realtime, Infra).

Voice Microservice: Node.js (TypeScript), Mediasoup for WebRTC, communicating with the .NET backend via gRPC.

Client: Tauri wrapping an Angular frontend.

Deployment: Docker Compose.

Rules:

Never mix logic between the Node.js voice service and the .NET text service.

Always use CSS variables (Custom Properties) in the Angular client for the theming engine.

Write clean, strongly typed code. Ensure EF Core migrations are created for all database changes.
